Issues.Body:
* .NET Core Version: 5.0.101
* Windows version: Windows10 20H2
* Does the bug reproduce also in WPF for .NET Framework 4.8?: Yes

 <!-- Read https://github.com/dotnet/wpf/blob/master/Documentation/issue-guide.md -->
 
 **Problem description:**

 If you repeat playing a video that contains "#" in the file name with MediaPlayer, the video will not play.
 This only happens if the video path contains a "#".
 
 **Actual behavior:** <!-- callstack for crashes / exceptions -->

 System.IO.FileNotFoundException: メディア ファイルが見つかりません。

 **Expected behavior:**
 
Video files containing "#" in the path can also be played normally.

 **Minimal repro:**

Code
``` cs
public partial class MainWindow : Window
{
    private MediaPlayer _player;

    public MainWindow()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Task.Run(PlayLoop);
    }

    private async Task PlayLoop()
    {
        //Uri uri = new Uri(@"E:\Work2\sample$1.mp4", UriKind.Absolute); // OK
        Uri uri = new Uri(@"E:\Work2\sample#1.mp4", UriKind.Absolute); // NG

        while (true)
        {
            Dispatcher.Invoke(() => Play(uri));
            await Task.Delay(2000);
        }
    }

    private void Play(Uri uri)
    {
        Debug.WriteLine($"Play: {uri}");

        _player?.Close();

        _player = new MediaPlayer();
        _player.MediaOpened += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("MediaOpened");
        _player.MediaEnded += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("MediaEnded");
        _player.MediaFailed += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine("MediaFailed:" + e.ErrorException);

        // view
        //this.grid.Background = new DrawingBrush(new VideoDrawing() { Rect = new Rect(0, 0, 1, 1), Player = _player });

        _player.Open(uri);
        _player.Play();
    }
}
```

